1
00:00:10,133 --> 00:00:11,533
You're Enzo's dad?

2
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:12,700
Yes, I am.

3
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,700
We were with him
when he was shot.

4
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,900
Who did this to my son?

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:17,933
There was a man.

6
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:20,367
It looked like Enzo
was his target.

7
00:00:20,467 --> 00:00:21,867
But my brother was there.

8
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:24,400
He fought with the gunman,
but he was shot too.

9
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:26,300
What's your brother's name?

10
00:00:26,433 --> 00:00:27,867
Samuel Trinidad.

11
00:00:29,167 --> 00:00:30,900
Have you heard?

12
00:00:31,067 --> 00:00:32,267
Heard what?

13
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:34,467
Trinidad was shot.

14
00:00:34,633 --> 00:00:36,600
Huh?
We just confirmed last night

15
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:38,933
that his son was kidnapped
by a scammer.

16
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,300
And now he was shot?

17
00:00:40,467 --> 00:00:41,633
Unbelievable.

18
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:43,633
What are you doing here?

19
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:44,967
Came to visit Samuel?

20
00:00:45,133 --> 00:00:47,333
Our other officemates
are coming.

21
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:48,467
Liar.

22
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:50,933
I killed his fellow scammers.

23
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:55,067
So when he wakes up,
tell him to watch out.

24
00:00:55,167 --> 00:00:57,067
He might be next.

25
00:00:59,333 --> 00:01:01,000
Enzo was shot?!
What happened?!

26
00:01:01,133 --> 00:01:03,933
Enzo was the target,
but Trinidad was hit too.

27
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:05,067
Who would do this?

28
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:06,433
Who do you think?!

29
00:01:06,533 --> 00:01:07,767
Who else could've done this?

30
00:01:07,900 --> 00:01:08,867
Diaz!

31
00:01:09,867 --> 00:01:12,000
Tell me what I need to do.

32
00:01:12,167 --> 00:01:13,267
Take him down!

33
00:01:13,367 --> 00:01:14,667
Leave it to me.

34
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:17,200
Roldan knows that
I ordered his son to be killed.

35
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:19,933
He's going to retaliate.

36
00:01:20,033 --> 00:01:21,033
[GUNSHOTS]

37
00:01:21,167 --> 00:01:22,100
Get him!

38
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:29,367
[GUNSHOTS]

39
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,533
- [KICK, BLOW LAND]
- [GUN CLATTERS]

40
00:01:31,667 --> 00:01:32,967
- [FLESH SQUELCHES]
- [GROANS]

41
00:01:34,500 --> 00:01:37,133
- [FLESH SQUELCHING]
- [LAUGHS MANIACALLY]

42
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:42,533
The surgery is done.

43
00:01:42,700 --> 00:01:45,067
He lost a lot of blood.

44
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:48,000
We'll do everything we can
for him to recover.

45
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:51,733
Daddy?

46
00:01:55,167 --> 00:01:56,533
Thank goodness!

47
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:59,033
I was so scared, Daddy!

48
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:03,000
I thought you were
going to leave me.

49
00:02:03,167 --> 00:02:06,567
I told you,
I'm not going anywhere.

50
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:19,633
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

51
00:02:37,567 --> 00:02:44,600
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

52
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:48,200
- Miss Lolita?
- Hmm?

53
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:49,233
I'm going home.

54
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,233
Oh, okay.

55
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,567
Just give me a call
if you need anything.

56
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:54,400
Yes. Thank you.

57
00:02:54,567 --> 00:02:56,267
- Thank you, too.
- Take care.

58
00:03:01,767 --> 00:03:03,433
[AGNES] How do you feel?

59
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,067
You scared me there.

60
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:08,933
Are you hungry, son?

61
00:03:09,100 --> 00:03:10,400
Are you in pain?

62
00:03:10,567 --> 00:03:14,267
Ma, I'm okay.

63
00:03:14,433 --> 00:03:15,900
Don't worry.

64
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:21,533
Get well soon, Samuel, okay?

65
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:28,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

66
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:38,800
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

67
00:03:46,467 --> 00:03:48,167
Enzo.

68
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:49,900
[EXHALES LOUDLY]

69
00:03:52,133 --> 00:03:53,067
Samuel.

70
00:03:55,967 --> 00:04:03,000
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

71
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:06,667
He's my father.

72
00:04:08,867 --> 00:04:10,133
I know him, son.

73
00:04:12,167 --> 00:04:13,167
He works for me.

74
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:20,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

75
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,467
Thank you very much
for saving my son, Samuel.

76
00:04:35,867 --> 00:04:39,333
You're welcome, Sir Roldan.

77
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:48,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

78
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:52,167
You are...

79
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,967
my son's boss?

80
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:57,633
Yes, ma'am.

81
00:04:57,733 --> 00:05:00,000
[ARISSA ON CALL]
 Auntie, King is missing.

82
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,633
What?!

83
00:05:01,767 --> 00:05:06,600
[KING ON VIDEO]
 Help me! Save me!

84
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:09,900
Dad, help me!

85
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:11,867
[PAENG] Maybe it's
 one of your father's victims.

86
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:16,900
No. Those people are desperate
but not evil.

87
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:18,700
A criminal did this.

88
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:21,933
Only Roldan and Jacob
could've done this.

89
00:05:22,767 --> 00:05:25,367
I'm glad you were able to visit.

90
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:31,067
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

91
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:32,900
By the way,

92
00:05:33,067 --> 00:05:35,367
don't worry about
your hospital bill.

93
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:36,967
I'll cover it.

94
00:05:38,633 --> 00:05:39,867
Sir...

95
00:05:39,967 --> 00:05:41,200
Sir, that won't be necessary.

96
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:42,967
No. I insist.

97
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:46,600
[PAENG] Auntie.

98
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:48,400
Let's step outside.

99
00:05:48,567 --> 00:05:51,467
Excuse us. We'll leave you
two alone to talk.

100
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:52,467
Let's go, Auntie.

101
00:05:54,667 --> 00:05:56,400
Come on, Auntie. Let's go!

102
00:05:56,567 --> 00:05:58,267
[MAEL] Let's go, Auntie.

103
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,933
Ma.

104
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:04,100
Samuel, we'll be outside.

105
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,967
Come on, Auntie.

106
00:06:13,133 --> 00:06:20,167
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:25,600
I don't know how
I could repay you

108
00:06:25,767 --> 00:06:28,133
for what you did
for my son.

109
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:34,967
I don't know what I would do
if I lost him.

110
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:39,900
I know how it feels...

111
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:44,967
to almost lose your son.

112
00:06:45,067 --> 00:06:46,533
I know exactly how it feels,
sir.

113
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:49,633
My son was kidnapped.

114
00:06:51,567 --> 00:06:56,333
Enzo helped me find him.

115
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:59,467
That's why
when I saw Enzo in danger,

116
00:06:59,567 --> 00:07:01,000
I didn't think twice.

117
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:04,467
I did what I had to.

118
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:09,100
For that, Samuel,
I can't thank you enough.

119
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,367
Sir, I would do it again.

120
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,133
Not because he's your son,

121
00:07:15,333 --> 00:07:17,633
or because
he's my sister's friend.

122
00:07:20,033 --> 00:07:22,200
Sir, Enzo is like family to me.

123
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:29,367
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

124
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:34,533
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

125
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:41,533
[LIQUID SLOSHING]

126
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:54,033
[LIQUID TRICKLING]

127
00:07:56,933 --> 00:07:58,567
[PLASTIC CONTAINER THUDS]

128
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,533
[LIGHTER CLICKS]

129
00:08:05,633 --> 00:08:12,500
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

130
00:08:21,567 --> 00:08:28,433
[FIRE CRACKLING]

131
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:50,433
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

132
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,800
- [DOOR OPENS]
- [MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

133
00:09:01,933 --> 00:09:04,467
Samuel, what did
that jerk tell you?

134
00:09:05,967 --> 00:09:06,900
Dear...

135
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,467
[WHISPERS] King is here.

136
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,800
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

137
00:09:11,933 --> 00:09:14,933
Uh, King, do you want
some ice cream?

138
00:09:15,033 --> 00:09:16,767
- Yes!
- Come, let's buy some.

139
00:09:16,867 --> 00:09:21,100
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

140
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:24,433
That monster!
He kidnapped my grandson!

141
00:09:24,533 --> 00:09:28,000
The nerve of him to offer
to pay your hospital bills!

142
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:31,500
What for? Did he think he could
bribe us?

143
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:33,500
[PAENG] Fortunately, I was
able to stop Auntie.

144
00:09:33,633 --> 00:09:35,700
Roldan would've ended up
in a hospital bed too.

145
00:09:35,867 --> 00:09:37,500
Oh, that's for sure!

146
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:41,333
And to think he has a son!

147
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:45,700
How could he stomach taking
other people's children?

148
00:09:45,867 --> 00:09:48,367
Does Enzo know
what his father does?

149
00:09:48,533 --> 00:09:49,967
I don't think so, Auntie.

150
00:09:50,067 --> 00:09:51,667
They're not on good terms.

151
00:09:51,833 --> 00:09:54,133
It's because his father
is evil.

152
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:55,500
He's not close with his dad.

153
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:58,267
That's why he works two jobs
to support himself.

154
00:09:59,867 --> 00:10:01,167
[SAMUEL] Arissa.

155
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:04,200
Don't tell Enzo
what you've found out.

156
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:09,067
I'm sure that he's unaware
of his father's crimes.

157
00:10:10,733 --> 00:10:11,633
Of course.

158
00:10:13,067 --> 00:10:15,667
It's just going to be hard
because he's my friend.

159
00:10:15,767 --> 00:10:17,533
I don't like keeping secrets.

160
00:10:17,667 --> 00:10:21,533
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

161
00:10:21,667 --> 00:10:26,500
Dear, what's your plan now?
What are you going to do?

162
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:31,533
[INHALES DEEPLY, SIGHS]

163
00:10:33,067 --> 00:10:35,500
Ma, I think it'd
be best...

164
00:10:36,767 --> 00:10:38,500
if you don't know
about it.

165
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,567
I'll take care of it.

166
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:44,067
Just trust me.

167
00:10:45,700 --> 00:10:47,700
I hope you understand.

168
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:52,933
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

169
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:56,400
[ENGINE HUMMING]

170
00:10:56,567 --> 00:10:59,900
[PHONE RINGING]

171
00:11:00,067 --> 00:11:01,500
Roldan.

172
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,567
Any news?

173
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:03,400
[SNICKERS]

174
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:04,867
It's done.

175
00:11:04,967 --> 00:11:06,700
I didn't just crush them.

176
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,333
I turned them to ashes.

177
00:11:08,467 --> 00:11:09,567
Great.

178
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:10,767
[LEAH] Hey!

179
00:11:10,933 --> 00:11:11,933
What happened?

180
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:13,233
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

181
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:14,367
Daddy!

182
00:11:14,467 --> 00:11:17,767
- What took you so long?
- Hi. Darling, come here.

183
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,300
[GRUNTS]

184
00:11:19,467 --> 00:11:22,267
I'm sorry. I had a lot
to finish at work.

185
00:11:22,433 --> 00:11:24,967
But I'll make it up to you.
I'm sorry.

186
00:11:26,267 --> 00:11:27,233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

187
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:29,633
Hon, what happened here?

188
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:33,967
[GROANS] Argh!

189
00:11:35,933 --> 00:11:38,433
- [JACOB GRUNTING]
- [FLESH SQUELCHING]

190
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:43,933
Must be the shaving.

191
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:46,400
Yeah. It's okay.
It's just a small cut.

192
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:49,467
Be careful next time, okay?

193
00:11:49,633 --> 00:11:51,133
Yeah. Come on.

194
00:11:51,267 --> 00:11:52,767
Let's get your ice cream.

195
00:11:52,867 --> 00:11:55,067
- Come on, hon.
- Mmm!

196
00:11:55,167 --> 00:11:57,467
- Ice cream!
- What flavor?

197
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:13,000
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:12:13,167 --> 00:12:14,433
- Chloe--
- [LOLITA GASPS]

199
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:22,200
[JACOB] Darling, here you go.

200
00:12:26,633 --> 00:12:27,500
Hon.

201
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:29,667
Who is it?

202
00:12:30,567 --> 00:12:31,333
Um...

203
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:34,100
I just thought I saw someone.

204
00:12:34,833 --> 00:12:36,333
Okay. Let's go.

205
00:12:36,500 --> 00:12:37,800
Let's go.

206
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:44,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

207
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,900
What time
did the incident happen?

208
00:12:50,033 --> 00:12:53,400
Around 10 in the morning.

209
00:12:53,533 --> 00:12:55,467
Did you recognize the gunman?

210
00:12:55,533 --> 00:12:57,733
I fought him
for his gun, but...

211
00:12:57,867 --> 00:12:59,167
I didn't recognize him.

212
00:13:02,067 --> 00:13:04,200
Have you been receiving
any death threats?

213
00:13:04,333 --> 00:13:06,133
Have you gotten into
a fight recently,

214
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:08,633
aside from the ones
happening to you

215
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:10,067
and your family currently?

216
00:13:10,233 --> 00:13:14,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

217
00:13:14,433 --> 00:13:15,700
I can't think of any.

218
00:13:18,867 --> 00:13:20,633
How's your father's case going?

219
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:23,700
The investment scam?

220
00:13:23,867 --> 00:13:25,100
Has it been resolved?

221
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:31,067
I don't know.
I don't have any updates.

222
00:13:31,233 --> 00:13:33,233
Weren't you involved
in his transactions?

223
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:35,400
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

224
00:13:35,567 --> 00:13:38,267
I had nothing to do with that.

225
00:13:40,767 --> 00:13:42,900
You are one tough cookie.

226
00:13:43,033 --> 00:13:44,100
So glad you're okay.

227
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:45,500
Thanks, Auntie.

228
00:13:49,567 --> 00:13:51,533
We live in dangerous times, huh?

229
00:13:53,367 --> 00:13:56,900
What if you stay
with your dad for now?

230
00:13:59,067 --> 00:14:02,200
Auntie, I'm fine staying
in my condo.

231
00:14:04,167 --> 00:14:05,467
Fine.

232
00:14:05,633 --> 00:14:07,433
If you don't want to live
with your dad,

233
00:14:07,567 --> 00:14:09,267
why don't you
stay with us first?

234
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,700
Honestly, Auntie...

235
00:14:13,933 --> 00:14:15,700
I'm okay.

236
00:14:17,433 --> 00:14:20,400
Enzo, don't be stubborn.

237
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,867
Let us take care of you.

238
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,267
Pa, Auntie...

239
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:28,600
I appreciate your concerns...

240
00:14:28,767 --> 00:14:31,467
but this time,
trust me on this.

241
00:14:32,867 --> 00:14:33,967
I'm all grown up.

242
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:40,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

243
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:45,733
If you were to ask me,

244
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:48,267
I'd assume you got
into a fight with someone.

245
00:14:48,367 --> 00:14:50,900
Maybe one of your father's
scam victims

246
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:52,467
or one of your victims.

247
00:14:52,633 --> 00:14:54,800
They're the ones
who might have a motive.

248
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:56,333
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

249
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:59,500
Is this still about
the shooting?

250
00:14:59,667 --> 00:15:02,233
Your line of questioning
sounds a bit odd.

251
00:15:02,367 --> 00:15:04,367
Relax, this is just the routine.
I'm just asking some--

252
00:15:04,533 --> 00:15:06,600
It sounds like
you're accusing me of something.

253
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:08,933
I'm just doing my job,
Mr. Trinidad.

254
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:13,867
But if you are hiding something,
you can tell us now.

255
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:15,200
It's a waste of an opportunity.

256
00:15:15,367 --> 00:15:16,600
Are you finished?

257
00:15:17,733 --> 00:15:20,000
If you are, you can go
so that I can rest.

258
00:15:21,033 --> 00:15:23,667
Unless you want to suggest
that I'm involved in the scam?

259
00:15:25,367 --> 00:15:27,100
I don't have any more questions.

260
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,667
Thank you for your cooperation.

261
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:34,700
I don't know, but I feel like
there's some distance

262
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:37,333
between Enzo and his dad.

263
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:42,533
By the way, hon,
you said someone helped Enzo?

264
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:49,867
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [DOOR CLOSES]

265
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:52,167
Well, I want to meet him.

266
00:15:52,267 --> 00:15:54,333
Uh, I just wanted to thank him.

267
00:15:54,433 --> 00:15:56,700
Do you know
what his room number is?

268
00:15:56,867 --> 00:15:57,833
He's resting.

269
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:02,300
They thanked him
a while ago.

270
00:16:05,833 --> 00:16:07,133
He's asleep.

271
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:08,833
Chloe.

272
00:16:08,967 --> 00:16:10,867
Let's go.
Come on.

273
00:16:10,967 --> 00:16:17,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

274
00:16:19,033 --> 00:16:25,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

275
00:16:31,933 --> 00:16:33,033
Ma?

276
00:16:33,133 --> 00:16:34,833
- Ma? Are you okay?
- Hmm?

277
00:16:36,267 --> 00:16:38,167
It looks like
you've seen a ghost.

278
00:16:38,267 --> 00:16:40,100
I'm okay.

279
00:16:40,267 --> 00:16:41,700
Do I not look okay?

280
00:16:42,933 --> 00:16:44,300
You look very serious.

281
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:48,767
It's nothing.

282
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:49,867
It's just...

283
00:16:53,567 --> 00:16:54,800
Hi, Sir Samuel.

284
00:16:54,967 --> 00:16:57,033
The doctor signed
your discharge papers.

285
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:58,467
You're free to go home.

286
00:16:58,633 --> 00:17:00,767
- Oh, thank goodness.
- Yay!

287
00:17:00,933 --> 00:17:07,767
[BRIGHT MUSIC PLAYING]

288
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:19,200
- [SOBBING]
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

289
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:20,667
- What's going on?
- Sir.

290
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,133
We have another
missing person.

291
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:23,800
He was recruited
as a programmer.

292
00:17:24,667 --> 00:17:26,567
And then he suddenly vanished.

293
00:17:29,633 --> 00:17:32,300
How long has it been
since your son left?

294
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:34,933
[SNIFFLING]
Around six months, sir.

295
00:17:36,267 --> 00:17:38,133
At first...

296
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:41,000
he would constantly update me.

297
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:45,733
He would always send me
his paycheck.

298
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:49,000
But we would only talk
through messages.

299
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:53,933
Whenever I try to call him,
he won't answer.

300
00:17:55,067 --> 00:17:57,167
How long has it been
since you two last talked?

301
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:58,600
[SOBBING]

302
00:17:58,700 --> 00:18:00,333
It's been 3 weeks, sir.

303
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:03,800
I have a bad feeling about this.

304
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:06,933
My son would never do that.

305
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:10,967
Miss, come here.
Let's look over here.

306
00:18:11,067 --> 00:18:12,267
[SNIFFLING]

307
00:18:12,367 --> 00:18:15,167
Not to scare you
or anything, miss.

308
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:18,767
But we've been getting a lot
of missing person cases.

309
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:25,933
They all suddenly vanished
after accepting a job offer.

310
00:18:26,067 --> 00:18:28,900
As you can see,
most of the missing men

311
00:18:29,067 --> 00:18:30,900
are programmers.

312
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:34,633
As for the women,
they're mostly models.

313
00:18:35,867 --> 00:18:39,067
We think they're victims
of human trafficking.

314
00:18:39,233 --> 00:18:43,700
[SOBBING] My poor son...

315
00:18:43,867 --> 00:18:48,633
- [SNIFFLING, SOBBING]
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

316
00:18:48,733 --> 00:18:51,367
But don't worry, miss.

317
00:18:53,433 --> 00:18:55,633
I'll help you
find your son, okay?

318
00:18:56,633 --> 00:18:58,733
Thank you so much, sir.

319
00:18:59,733 --> 00:19:01,733
You are heaven-sent.

320
00:19:02,867 --> 00:19:05,600
I'll go now, sir. [SNIFFLES]

321
00:19:09,033 --> 00:19:12,900
[SAMUEL] Roldan is also
targeting fellow criminals.

322
00:19:13,933 --> 00:19:17,933
A lot of money is at stake,
so they're all ready to fight.

323
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:21,567
Dude, this situation
has gone overboard.

324
00:19:21,733 --> 00:19:24,367
Are you sure you want to
infiltrate Roldan's group?

325
00:19:25,567 --> 00:19:27,400
[MAEL] Yeah, dude.
You might...

326
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:31,600
end up with more than just
some bruises and a bullet wound.

327
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:34,267
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

328
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:35,467
Maybe you can...

329
00:19:36,467 --> 00:19:41,933
get some of the money and use it
to hire a hitman for those two.

330
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:46,967
100 million might be enough
as a reward.

331
00:19:47,133 --> 00:19:48,900
[SAMUEL]
I doubt that would work.

332
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,567
Their operations
have a huge reach.

333
00:19:51,667 --> 00:19:54,800
There is someone
bigger in charge.

334
00:19:54,967 --> 00:19:57,900
Even if those two disappears,
someone will replace them.

335
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:01,100
Which means their schemes
will have no end.

336
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:03,233
This will only work
in their favor.

337
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:07,900
Because we won't know
who'll replace them.

338
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:10,500
That's true.

339
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:12,267
So dudes,
even if it's dangerous,

340
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,800
I need to finish my mission.

341
00:20:17,167 --> 00:20:20,300
I need to uncover
all their secrets.

342
00:20:20,467 --> 00:20:27,300
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

343
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:47,533
What I am offering you
is a chance for a fresh start.

344
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:49,967
Help me.
Clean your name.

345
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:52,133
You didn't just risk your life
for someone.

346
00:20:52,300 --> 00:20:54,600
And I will be forever
grateful to you.

347
00:20:54,733 --> 00:20:56,833
Sir, I see you all
as my family.

348
00:20:56,967 --> 00:20:59,000
Now I'm worried about
what you're planning to do.

349
00:20:59,133 --> 00:21:00,600
We just received
an initial order.

350
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:02,000
They need to conduct

351
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:05,100
- an audit at Oriental Ridge.
- What?!

352
00:21:05,233 --> 00:21:09,767
This is our only way to get
enough evidence against them.

353
00:21:09,933 --> 00:21:12,400
Sins of the Father.
